messageBody:
Hello, all. I just joined this fine group today, as I'm very
interested in the Read Alphabet. I've been practicing it for a while
now, and reading the manual, and I'm quite impressed on how developed
this alphabet is. I've come up with my own alhpabets for the English
language, but this one was definitely the result of quite a bit of
effort, much more than I've ever put in.

So anyway, that's my little spiel. I've been messing around with the
Jerome font, and I've written a couple little things in Word. If
anyone would like to see them, or the alphabets I've made, feel free
to reply and ask for them, I'd be happy to put them up for all to see.

I have a question for everyone. How/for what do YOU use Quikscript?
Personally, I'm just starting, but I plan to possibly take notes in
college, and make little notes to myself, or possibly use it as a
code to exchange notes with friends. Mostly for taking/making notes,
though. Anyway, that's about all I have to say. Hope to get some
replies soon!

Charles Smith
